				<a href="//dotearth.blogs.nytimes.com/2016/11/30/teds-science-curator-sees-hope-in-the-anthropocene/"><img src="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2016/11/29/blogs/dotunnatural/dotunnatural-thumbStandard.jpg" width="50" height="50" /></a>
			</div>
							<h6 class="kicker">
					<a href="//dotearth.blogs.nytimes.com/category/anthropocene-2/">Anthropocene</a>
				</h6>
							<h5><a href="//dotearth.blogs.nytimes.com/2016/11/30/teds-science-curator-sees-hope-in-the-anthropocene/" title="Read: TED&#8217;s Science Curator Sees Hope in Earth&#8217;s Anthropocene Age">TED&#8217;s Science Curator Sees Hope in Earth&#8217;s Anthropocene Age</a>
			<span class="postMetaHeaderCommentCount commentCount hidden">
					<i class="icon"></i>
					<a class="commentCountLink commentCountNumberOnly commentCountNoPrompt" href="//dotearth.blogs.nytimes.com/2016/11/30/teds-science-curator-sees-hope-in-the-anthropocene/"></a>
				</span>			</h5>
			<p class="summary">
			TED&#8217;s new curator of science, David Biello, explains why he sees hints of hope in Earth&#8217;s emerging Anthropocene &#8220;age of us.&#8221;<a href="//dotearth.blogs.nytimes.com/2016/11/30/teds-science-curator-sees-hope-in-the-anthropocene/" class="more-link">Read&#160;more&#8230;</a></p>
